---
import DsSectionHeader from "./DsSectionHeader.astro";

interface Props {
  isIsolated?: boolean;
  isolatedComponentId?: string;
}
const { isIsolated = false } = Astro.props;
---

<DsSectionHeader
  title="Layout System"
  url={isIsolated ? "/resources/design-system" : "/resources/design-system/layout"}
  isIsolated={isIsolated}
/>

<p>The Avionics layout system uses a sophisticated CSS Grid approach for responsive, content-focused layouts. Every page shares the same <code>.grid-layout</code> applied to <code>&lt;main&gt;</code> in <code>BaseLayout.astro</code>.</p>

<h3>Prose Contexts</h3>
<p>We distinguish between generic prose and article content:</p>
<ul>
  <li><code>.prose</code>: Generic typography styles for any text block. Uses <code>display: contents</code> so children participate directly in the parent grid.</li>
  <li><code>.content-prose</code>: Enhanced styles for long-form articles, including specific spacing for headings and lists.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Spacing Tokens</h3>
<pre><code>--s-grid-unit: 0.5em;          /* Fundamental grid unit */
--s-gutter-min: var(--s-grid-unit); /* Minimum gutter width */
--s-gutter-max: 9.7ch;         /* Maximum gutter width */
--s-content-max: 67ch;         /* Optimal reading width */
--s-grid: 24px;                /* Base grid unit (components) */
--s-gap: 1.5rem;               /* Standard gap between elements */</code></pre>

<h3>Content Grid</h3>
<p>The <code>.grid-layout</code> class defines a 6-column symmetric grid with three named content zones. This is the backbone of every page.</p>

<pre><code>.grid-layout {`{`}
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns:
    [full-start]     minmax(var(--s-gutter-min), 1fr)
    [breakout-start] minmax(var(--s-gutter-min), var(--s-gutter-max))
    [content-start]  min(100% - 4 * var(--s-grid-unit), var(--s-content-max))
    [content-end]
                     minmax(var(--s-gutter-min), var(--s-gutter-max)) [breakout-end]
                     minmax(var(--s-gutter-min), 1fr)                 [full-end];
{`}`}</code></pre>

<h4>Column Map</h4>

<div class="ds-grid-diagram" aria-label="Content grid column diagram">
  <div class="ds-grid-row ds-grid-row--labels">
    <span class="ds-grid-label">full</span>
    <span class="ds-grid-label">gutter</span>
    <span class="ds-grid-label">content (67ch)</span>
    <span class="ds-grid-label">gutter</span>
    <span class="ds-grid-label">full</span>
  </div>
  <div class="ds-grid-row ds-grid-row--full">
    <div class="ds-grid-bar ds-grid-bar--full">
      <code>grid-column: full</code>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="ds-grid-row ds-grid-row--breakout">
    <div class="ds-grid-spacer"></div>
    <div class="ds-grid-bar ds-grid-bar--breakout">
      <code>grid-column: breakout</code>
    </div>
    <div class="ds-grid-spacer"></div>
  </div>
  <div class="ds-grid-row ds-grid-row--content">
    <div class="ds-grid-spacer"></div>
    <div class="ds-grid-spacer"></div>
    <div class="ds-grid-bar ds-grid-bar--content">
      <code>grid-column: content</code>
    </div>
    <div class="ds-grid-spacer"></div>
    <div class="ds-grid-spacer"></div>
  </div>
</div>

<h4>Zone Widths</h4>
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Zone</th>
      <th>Named lines</th>
      <th>Width</th>
      <th>Use case</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td><code>content</code></td>
      <td><code>content-start</code> / <code>content-end</code></td>
      <td>max 67ch</td>
      <td>Body text, headings, lists &mdash; optimal reading measure</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><code>breakout</code></td>
      <td><code>breakout-start</code> / <code>breakout-end</code></td>
      <td>content + 2 &times; 9.7ch gutters</td>
      <td>Tables, figures, code blocks, diagrams</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><code>full</code></td>
      <td><code>full-start</code> / <code>full-end</code></td>
      <td>100% viewport</td>
      <td>Hero sections, full-bleed backgrounds</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h4>Default Placement</h4>
<p>All direct children of <code>.grid-layout</code> default to the <strong>content</strong> column. Opt in to wider zones with utility classes:</p>
<pre><code>.grid-layout &gt; *          {`{`} grid-column: content;  {`}`}  /* default */
.grid-layout &gt; .breakout  {`{`} grid-column: breakout; {`}`}
.grid-layout &gt; .full      {`{`} grid-column: full; width: 100%; {`}`}</code></pre>

<h4>Live Demo</h4>
<p>The bars below are placed inside the page's <code>.grid-layout</code> to show real column boundaries:</p>

<div class="ds-grid-demo ds-grid-demo--content">
  <span class="ds-grid-demo-label">content</span>
  <span class="ds-grid-demo-note">Default zone &mdash; body text lives here (67ch max)</span>
</div>
<div class="ds-grid-demo ds-grid-demo--breakout breakout">
  <span class="ds-grid-demo-label">breakout</span>
  <span class="ds-grid-demo-note">Tables, figures, and code blocks expand into gutters</span>
</div>
<div class="ds-grid-demo ds-grid-demo--full full">
  <span class="ds-grid-demo-label">full</span>
  <span class="ds-grid-demo-note">Edge-to-edge &mdash; hero sections, full-bleed backgrounds</span>
</div>

<h4>Automatic Breakout</h4>
<p>Some elements break out automatically via CSS rules in <code>prose.css</code> and <code>grid.css</code> &mdash; no class needed:</p>
<ul>
  <li><code>table</code> inside <code>.prose</code> &rarr; <code>breakout</code></li>
  <li><code>figure</code> inside <code>.prose</code> &rarr; <code>breakout</code></li>
</ul>

<h4>Prose &amp; Grid Integration</h4>
<p>The <code>.prose</code> class uses <code>display: contents</code>, which makes its children direct grid participants. This is what allows markdown-rendered content (headings, paragraphs, tables) to align to named grid columns without extra wrapper markup:</p>
<pre><code>.grid-layout &gt; .prose {`{`} display: contents; {`}`}
.prose &gt; *             {`{`} grid-column: content; {`}`}
.prose &gt; table          {`{`} grid-column: breakout !important; {`}`}</code></pre>

<h3>Spec Grid</h3>
<p>A responsive grid for card collections (Concepts, Patterns, Practices):</p>
<pre><code>.spec-grid {`{`}
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr));
  gap: var(--s-gap);
{`}`}</code></pre>

<style>
  /* --- Grid Column Diagram --- */
  .ds-grid-diagram {
    border: 1px solid var(--c-border);
    padding: 1rem 0;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    background: var(--c-bg-surface);
    font-family: var(--f-mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
  }

  .ds-grid-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 3fr 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 2px;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.5rem;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .ds-grid-row--labels {
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--c-border);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .ds-grid-label {
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--c-text-secondary);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .ds-grid-bar {
    padding: 0.5rem;
    text-align: center;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }

  .ds-grid-bar code {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    background: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .ds-grid-bar--full {
    grid-column: 1 / -1;
    background: var(--c-brand);
    color: var(--c-bg-page);
  }
  .ds-grid-bar--full code { color: var(--c-bg-page); }

  .ds-grid-bar--breakout {
    grid-column: 2 / 5;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--c-brand) 30%, transparent);
    color: var(--c-text-primary);
  }

  .ds-grid-bar--content {
    grid-column: 3 / 4;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--c-brand) 15%, transparent);
    color: var(--c-text-primary);
  }

  .ds-grid-spacer {
    /* empty grid cell */
  }

  /* --- Live Demo Bars --- */
  .ds-grid-demo {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
    font-family: var(--f-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }

  .ds-grid-demo-label {
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .ds-grid-demo-note {
    color: var(--c-text-secondary);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
  }

  .ds-grid-demo--content {
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--c-brand) 10%, transparent);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--c-brand);
  }

  .ds-grid-demo--breakout {
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--c-brand) 20%, transparent);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--c-brand);
  }

  .ds-grid-demo--full {
    background: var(--c-brand);
    color: var(--c-bg-page);
    border-left: none;
  }
  .ds-grid-demo--full .ds-grid-demo-note {
    color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--c-bg-page) 80%, transparent);
  }
</style>
